column14: Talked awhile with an older farmer. His family had been farming that land for over 100 years. He mentioned a big die-off of Emel around 2003, but they have rebounded and are doing well in the area now. The rebound interestingly corresponded to the same time that a big mine(?) in the region stopped burning sulfur dioxide. He mentioned good, healthy wild stands on his land further up Kara Springs Rd and that his family had planted 1000 trees recently. Also mentioned 6 suicides mostly young farm men in as many recent years. Very tough morale for farmers, especially hitting the young guys, uff.
